{ Since White's light-squared Bishop has already been given the task of supporting the Knight on f3, it is unlikely that it will be redeployed to b5 to pin the Knight. }
7. O-O e6 8. Ne5 Bxe2
{ A common idea in the Caro-Kann, as is also the case with the French Defense, is for Black to rid themselves of their light-squared Bishop.  Note that at this point, five of Black's seven pawns are on light squares.  This is not usual in this opening, so the light squares are strong, and Black's light-squared Bishop is not as important. }
